            "When Majoni roasts rice flour until it crackles and turns golden, she is triggering the **Maillard reaction** \u2014 one of the most important chemical reactions in cooking. It is not the same as caramelization, although they look similar. The Maillard reaction happens when **amino acids** (from proteins) react with **reducing sugars** at temperatures above roughly 140 \u00b0C.",
