            'Coexistence works when people understand which animals are genuinely dangerous and which are harmless or beneficial. In India, of the approximately 300 snake species, only about 60 are venomous, and only 4 (the "Big Four" — Indian cobra, common krait, Russell\'s viper, and saw-scaled viper) account for most snakebite deaths. Rock pythons, like Bornali, are non-venomous constrictors that pose virtually no threat to humans. Yet fear of all snakes leads to indiscriminate killing, which removes beneficial pest controllers from the ecosystem.',
